      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;square-shaped-animations&#34;&gt;Square-shaped animations&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;about-these-animations&#34;&gt;About these animations&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I created these animations using the R programming language. The animations are based on randomness. Random walks were used to create unpredictable changes in colors or of objects moving on the canvas.&#xA;In some animations, I combined the R-created footage with pictures or movies that I found on the internet or recorded with my mobile phone.&#xA;I started making these animations during my PhD, probably around 2013.&#xA;The viewer below plays the animations in a random order, so it is a different experience for every viewer.&#xA;In case you don&amp;rsquo;t see any animations here, it could be due to the browser settings.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
